Cloud integration allows connecting Anori to backend services. It's guarded by `CLOUD_INTEGRATION_ENABLED` flag (development only).

The app uses tRPC with React Query integration. The tRPC client is automatically provided through `TRPCProvider` which wraps `QueryClientProvider`.

# Feature Flag

```ts
import { CLOUD_INTEGRATION_ENABLED } from '@anori/cloud-integration/consts';

// Use to conditionally render UI
{CLOUD_INTEGRATION_ENABLED && <CloudFeature />}
```

# Check Connection Status

## In React Components

```ts
import { useCloudAccount } from '@anori/cloud-integration/hooks';

const MyComponent = () => {
  const { account, isConnected, isLoading, status } = useCloudAccount();
  
  // account: { sessionToken, email, userId } | null
  // isConnected: boolean
  // isLoading: boolean (initial load state)
  // status: 'connected' | 'not-connected'
  
  if (isConnected && account) {
    return <div>Logged in as {account.email}</div>;
  }
  return <div>Not connected</div>;
};
```

## Outside React (Imperative)

```ts
import { getCloudAccount } from '@anori/cloud-integration/storage';

const account = getCloudAccount(); // { sessionToken, email, userId } | null
const token = account?.sessionToken; // string | undefined
```

# Using the API Client

## With React Query (Recommended)

Use tRPC hooks from `@anori/cloud-integration/api-client`. The client is automatically configured with authentication:

```ts
import { trpc } from '@anori/cloud-integration/api-client';

const MyComponent = () => {
  // Queries automatically use React Query
  const { data, isLoading, error } = trpc.user.profile.useQuery();
  
  // Mutations work the same way
  const updateProfile = trpc.user.updateProfile.useMutation({
    onSuccess: () => {
      console.log('Profile updated!');
    },
  });
  
  const handleUpdate = () => {
    updateProfile.mutate({ name: 'New Name' });
  };
  
  if (isLoading) return <div>Loading...</div>;
  if (error) return <div>Error: {error.message}</div>;
  
  return <div>Hello {data.name}</div>;
};
```

**Benefits**: Automatic caching, refetching, optimistic updates, and error handling through React Query.

## Imperative API Calls (Outside React or Special Cases)

```ts
import { getApiClient } from '@anori/cloud-integration/api-client';

const client = getApiClient();
const data = await client.user.profile.query();
```

Use imperative calls only when you can't use hooks (background scripts, utilities, etc.).

# Error Handling

Cloud API uses typed errors from `@anori-app/api-types`. Check error types with `isAppErrorOfType`:

```ts
import { isAppErrorOfType } from '@anori-app/api-client';
import { InvalidCredentialsError, RateLimitError } from '@anori-app/api-types';

try {
  await client.auth.login.mutate({ email, password });
} catch (e) {
  if (isAppErrorOfType(e, InvalidCredentialsError)) {
    // Handle invalid credentials
  } else if (isAppErrorOfType(e, RateLimitError)) {
    // Handle rate limit
  } else {
    // Handle unknown error
  }
}
```

**Never** use `instanceof` or check `error.name` - always use `isAppErrorOfType`.